<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3610] After reloading a core, indexing will fail on any newly added fields to the schema.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3610</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is just another instantiation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3587&quot; title=&quot;After reloading a SolrCore, the original Analyzer is still used rather than a new one.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3587&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3587&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the IndexWriter is kept open, the Codec still uses the old schema, and when asked to index for the field, doesn&apos;t know about it and returns an error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could dodge the problem for now by turning off per-field codec support by default, requiring users to turn it on explicitly in solrconfig.xml (like similarity), knowing they are making a tradeoff by doing that (same goes for Similarity if you are using a per-field configuration).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
