                            <comment id="13409869" author="rcmuir" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 21:28:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch dodging the problem. I tried cleaning this up to work like similarity (which, if you enable schema-based per-field sim support, has the exact same problem).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Needs a test.&lt;br/&gt;
Needs checks like what Hoss did in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3577&quot; title=&quot;better javadocs and error messages related to global/fieldtype SimilarityFactory usage&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3577&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3577&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13409906" author="rcmuir" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 22:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated patch with checks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13409986" author="rcmuir" created="Tue, 10 Jul 2012 00:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed this. I think the indexwriter config is a larger issue, so turning this off by default means a majority of people won&apos;t get bit by it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13412244" author="hossman" created="Wed, 11 Jul 2012 22:34:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hoss20120711-manual-post-40alpha-change&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13580335" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 18 Feb 2013 00:01:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should be able to fix this now that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4417&quot; title=&quot;Look into reopening the IndexWriter on core reload.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4417&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4417&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
